<subSubSection id="0E3BEC15CEAACE7B1A8D70BC318237A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="FDB3295834FB9473EFCFC2B6E0C7CD50" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7D7DDDB2DB545FA74D3283FF4C2F14F0" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New record: East Rhodopes, Bryagovets vill., 06.04.2013, 7 q. in a nest of 
<taxonomicName id="BD3E99540EB374D24AC2FC5B829BF3AD" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis id="168130E5DE1BFF731A822D14C2ACE005" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Plagiolepis pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Latreille, 1798), leg. ALG; Ograzhden Mt., Drakata vill., 09.09.2021, 6 q. in a nest of 
<taxonomicName id="95FBEE117C87C9C46B5F05C275545E58" genus="Pl." lsidName="Pl. pygmaea" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis id="91B33F6D50DF9914DF8808D1E33C87AE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Pl. pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="1943DBEC00A21B930F0E2F9E13EB2256" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="B28490C5F67A428F57217ADE0C1681A8" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="F53670315A59F79E7DF415D17B7C9A14" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2D9A668493F2137DC4DE73C6AAA8FDEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
First record for Bulgaria. 
<taxonomicName id="A0855E8256E04592AA3F08A003285DFF" authorityName="Staercke" authorityYear="1936" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis xene" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xene">
<emphasis id="62F4DEB731EE35D823200ADA8E20E0E3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Plagiolepis xene</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a rare workerless inquiline in nests of 
<taxonomicName id="157E43A8A3CFFF52404A8CCEF31ECD43" baseAuthorityName="Latreille" baseAuthorityYear="1798" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Plagiolepis" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Plagiolepis pygmaea" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pygmaea">
<emphasis id="28D5382E81EA44D88FB65DAB9C3C1CA4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Plagiolepis pygmaea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Its distribution range covers southern and central Europe to Anatolia.
</paragraph>
